var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"ErfJab","text":"<p>Hello, I'm Erfan! As an architecture student, I'm passionate about contributing to the open-source and free software community. I dedicate my free time and even occasional breaks to working on meaningful projects. This page showcases my work and provides comprehensive information about my projects in an organized framework.</p> <p>We all know that commercial projects may advance specific individuals, but open-source projects advance the entire community.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#my-projects","title":"My Projects","text":"<ul> <li>HolderBot: Telegram bot for Marzban panel management.</li> <li>Essl: Quick SSL certificate acquisition script.</li> <li>Backuper: Customizable automated backup script.</li> <li>WebTemplates: Various HTML templates for quick use.</li> <li>Sqlar: Telegram bot for SQL command execution.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#notable-contributions","title":"Notable Contributions","text":"<ul> <li>Marzban: An Xray-based management panel.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#contact","title":"Contact","text":"<p>Find me on:  GitHub |   Telegram |   Email</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/index.html","title":"Backuper","text":"<p>Backuper is an automated script designed for backing up files and directories from a Linux server. It supports various templates for Xray panel data and databases.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/index.html#features-of-backuper","title":"Features of Backuper","text":"<ul> <li>Automatic Backups: Schedule and manage backups automatically.</li> <li>Custom Cron Jobs: Set up your preferred cron jobs.</li> <li>Manage Active Backups: Delete existing active backups.</li> <li>Manage Auxiliary Backups: Remove extra backups.</li> <li>File and Directory Backup: Backup specific files and directories as needed.</li> <li>Telegram Integration: Send backup notifications to Telegram.</li> <li>Discord Integration: Send backup notifications to Discord.</li> <li>Compression Options: Choose your preferred compression method.</li> <li>Custom Backup Names: Name your backup files as desired.</li> <li>Timestamped Backups: Include date and time in backup filenames.</li> <li>Split Backups: Divide backup files into smaller parts.</li> <li>Partitioning: Manage file size limitations with partitioning.</li> <li>Advanced and Simple Settings: Choose between advanced or straightforward configurations.</li> <li>Caption Customization: Add captions to your backups.</li> <li>Support for 7z and ZIP: Backup files in both 7z and ZIP formats.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/index.html#backuper-templates","title":"Backuper Templates","text":"<ul> <li>Marzban</li> <li>All xui</li> <li>hiddify</li> <li>Custom</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/index.html#why-backuper","title":"Why Backuper?","text":""},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html","title":"Advanced Installation","text":""},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#template-selection","title":"Template Selection","text":"<p>Just like in the simple installation, select a template from the following options:</p> <ul> <li>Marzban</li> <li>xui</li> <li>Hiddify</li> <li>Custom: For users who need to create a tailored template.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#customization","title":"Customization","text":"<p>The advanced installation allows you to specify which files and directories should be included or excluded from the backup. For example:</p> <ul> <li>Include: <code>/home/user/important_files/</code></li> <li>Exclude: <code>/tmp/</code> or any temporary directories.</li> </ul> <p>This customization ensures that only the necessary data is backed up, optimizing storage and backup efficiency.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#backup-name","title":"Backup Name","text":"<p>Provide a descriptive name for your backup process. Examples include:</p> <ul> <li>Master</li> <li>BackupPanel</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#cron-job-configuration","title":"Cron Job Configuration","text":"<p>Set how often the backup should be performed by entering the interval in minutes. Examples include:</p> <ul> <li>Daily at Midnight: Enter <code>1440</code> minutes (24 hours).</li> <li>Weekly: Enter <code>10080</code> minutes (7 days).</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#caption","title":"Caption","text":"<p>Optionally, add a caption to describe the backup\u2019s contents or purpose. This can help with documentation and tracking. If not needed, you can skip this step by pressing Enter.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#compression-type","title":"Compression Type","text":"<p>Choose the compression format for your backup. We support two formats:</p> <ul> <li> <p>ZIP: A popular and widely-compatible format that is easy to use. ZIP files can be opened by most operating systems and archive utilities. It is suitable for general backup needs and is well-supported across different platforms.</p> </li> <li> <p>7z: Known for a higher compression ratio and more efficient data compression compared to ZIP. This format is ideal for larger backups where space efficiency is important. However, 7z files may require specific software (like 7-Zip) to open, which might not be as universally available as ZIP utilities.</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#destination","title":"Destination","text":"<p>Select the platform for sending your backups:</p> <ul> <li>Telegram</li> <li>Discord</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#telegram-integration","title":"Telegram Integration","text":"<p>You will need:</p> <ul> <li>Bot Token: Obtain this token by creating a Telegram bot.</li> <li>Chat ID: Find this in your Telegram chat or group settings.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#discord-integration","title":"Discord Integration","text":"<p>You will need:</p> <ul> <li>Webhook URL: Create this URL through Discord server settings.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/advenced_install.html#completion","title":"Completion","text":"<p>Your advanced backup configuration is complete. The backup process will follow the schedule and settings you\u2019ve defined. Be sure to star the Backuper repository on GitHub to support ongoing development and enhancements.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/install.html","title":"Installation Process","text":""},{"location":"Backuper/install.html#choosing-installation-type","title":"Choosing Installation Type","text":"<p>When setting up Backuper, you'll be asked to choose between two installation types: Simple and Advanced. </p> <ul> <li>Simple Installation: Ideal for users who need a straightforward backup solution with minimal configuration. It\u2019s quick and easy, perfect for basic backup needs.</li> <li>Advanced Installation: Offers more customization options, allowing you to tailor the backup process to specific requirements. This is ideal for users who need more control and flexibility.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/manage.html","title":"Management","text":"<p>In this section, you can view and manage your list of backups. You will be able to stop and delete any backup by entering its corresponding number.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html","title":"Simple Installation","text":""},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#template-selection","title":"Template Selection","text":"<p>The first step in the simple installation is to select a template that matches your requirements. We offer three pre-defined templates:</p> <ul> <li>Marzban: Suitable for backing up Marzban panel data.</li> <li>xui: Designed for xui panel configurations.</li> <li>Hiddify: Tailored for Hiddify setups.</li> </ul> <p>For example, if you are working with a Marzban panel, choose the Marzban template. This ensures that the backup is compatible with the specific data structures and settings of your panel.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#backup-name","title":"Backup Name","text":"<p>Assign a meaningful name to your backup process and file. This name helps you easily identify your backups later. For instance:</p> <ul> <li>Master</li> <li>BackupPanel</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#cron-job-setup","title":"Cron Job Setup","text":"<p>Specify how frequently you want the backup to run. Enter the interval in minutes. For example:</p> <ul> <li>Every hour: Enter <code>60</code>.</li> <li>Every day: Enter <code>1440</code> (which is 24 hours).</li> </ul> <p>This allows you to automate your backups to fit your schedule.</p>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#destination","title":"Destination","text":"<p>Choose where you want your backups to be sent. Backuper supports two platforms:</p> <ul> <li>Telegram</li> <li>Discord</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#telegram-integration","title":"Telegram Integration","text":"<p>For sending backups to Telegram, you\u2019ll need:</p> <ul> <li>Bot Token: This is an authentication token for your Telegram bot, which you can obtain by creating a bot on Telegram.</li> <li>Chat ID: A unique identifier for the Telegram chat where the backups will be sent.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#discord-integration","title":"Discord Integration","text":"<p>For Discord, you will need:</p> <ul> <li>Webhook URL: This URL allows you to post messages to a specified Discord channel. You can generate this URL in the Discord server settings.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"Backuper/simple_install.html#completion","title":"Completion","text":"<p>Once you\u2019ve configured these settings, your backup process will be set up and ready to start based on your chosen schedule. Remember to star the Backuper repository on GitHub to support ongoing development and improvements.</p>"}]}